snippet.title: Determine if an Equation is a Hyperbola, Ellipse, Parabola or Circle
snippet.description:
Learn how to classify conics easily from their equation in this free math video tutorial by Mario's Math Tutoring.  We discuss ellipses, hyperbolas, circles and parabolas.

0:08 General Form of a Conic
0:21 How to Determine if the Conic is an Ellipse, Circle, Parabola or Hyperbola

1:57 Example 1 3x^2 - 4y^2 +6x - 8y + 10 = 0 (Hyperbola)
2:25 Example 2 5x^2 + 5y^2 + 20x - 10y -8 = 0 (Circle)
2:44 Example 3 x^2 + 2y^2 - 3x + y + 2 = 0 (Ellipse)
3:09 Example 4 5x^2 + 2x + y - 8 = 0 (Parabola)
3:20 Example 5 3y^2 + y + 4x - 7 (Parabola)
